Git is a distributed version control system that tracks changes in source code by storing snapshots of project history. It enables collaboration, branching, rollback, and traceability of infrastructure or application changes.

git remote add origin https://github.com/<username>/devsecops-journey.git   >> add remote repo
git remote -v  >> check remote repos
git push -u origin master
git diff >> check changes to tracked files
git add >> working dir to stage
git status
after git add if we change anything we see the changes using git diff,then we can restore
git restore
